Swansea boss Garry Monk has responded to speculation linking him to the West Ham job by insisting the perfect man to manage the club is already in place at Upton Park .
Sam Allardyce 's current contract expires at the end of the season , and suggested West Ham 's owners might go in a different direction .
Monk has leading Swansea to a record-equalling 47 Barclays Premier League points with six games left .